  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      It is hypothesized that the long-term results of rehabilitation and subsequent aging after
      Brain Trauma depend on brain's premorbid anatomical (structural) and functional (cognitive,
      emotional) reserves.

      The purpose of this study are:

        1. to determine whether such reserves exist.

        2. to study their convergent and discriminant validity.

        3. to study their characteristics.
    </textblock>
